HotelCompany 1 -- * owns Hotel
A Hotel called owns has A HotelCompany. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one HotelCompany.
A HotelCompany has some Hotels called owns. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Hotel is created, its HotelCompany must be assigned. When a Hotel is deleted, its HotelCompany is not deleted and its list of Hotels is decreased. When a HotelCompany is deleted, its Hotels are not deleted. They are assigned to another HotelCompany.
